#import "template.typ": *

#let metadata = (
  title: "Area Solo Suitability Assessment and E13 Formal Assessment",
  unit: "Group A (3-Axis) | Phase 4 — Lesson 6 | Decision Gate + E13",
  author: "C.Moroney",
)

#let lesson = (
title: [Area Solo Suitability Assessment and E13 Formal Assessment]

,aim: [
Demonstrate all Phase 4 elements and full E13 competency in a connected student-planned flight, meet the second S standard requirement for E14, and confirm readiness for unsupervised training area solo operations.
]

,overview: [
Lesson 4.6 combines the area solo suitability assessment, the E14 second S standard flight, and the formal E13 assessment into a single flight. By this point the student has completed five Phase 4 lessons, each involving a departure, training area operations, and an overhead join. The student has had multiple opportunities to develop and consolidate radio procedures, the circuit departure and join, and all training area manoeuvres before any formal assessment occurs.

The student plans and conducts the complete flight as PIC. The instructor is a silent assessor throughout for both the manoeuvre elements and E13. No coaching or prompting is provided for any assessed item. If all requirements are met, area solo is authorised at the conclusion of this flight.
]

,learning_outcomes: [
No new learning outcomes — this is a milestone assessment and decision gate.
]

,theory_knowledge: [
- Consolidation of all Phase 4 reading
- Theory exam completion confirmed, or a solid plan to complete the remaining exams soon
]

,ground_brief_topics: [
Total time: 25 minutes \
Equipment required: Student training record, VNC, NAIPS access \

*Student Plans and Briefs the Complete Flight* (20 minutes)
- NAIPS: TAF/GAF/GPWT obtained and interpreted; conditions assessed; brief presented to instructor
- NOTAMs: checked; relevant items identified
- Maintenance release: reviewed; brief presented to instructor
- ERSA: student briefs home aerodrome and nominated alternate aerodrome ERSA entries: elevation, CTAF frequency, circuit direction, runway length, relevant remarks
- Route: departure, training area entry, manoeuvre sequence (E9, E10, E14, E16 in a logical order), training area exit, overhead join, circuit and landing
- HASSELL minimum heights for each exercise
- EFATO plan for today's runway and conditions
- Theory exam status: student confirms which exams are complete

*Assessment Criteria Brief* (5 minutes)
- Instructor confirms this is an assessment and decision gate — no coaching or prompting will be provided for any assessed item
- E14: if S standard is achieved today, it counts as the second S standard flight for area solo authorisation
- E13: assessed formally across the complete flight — radio calls, timing, active listening, transponder, airspace awareness, radio failure, and MAYDAY
- Assessment standard: P, S, C, or NC per element and per E13 competency variable
]

,ground_tasks:[
#text(size:12pt)[*Student leads all pre-flight administration completely independently.*]

#text(size:12pt)[*Instructor*]
- Receives full brief; may ask clarifying questions
- Confirms conditions are suitable for all planned exercises
- Provides no content input from this point
- Begins recording E13 competency variable assessments from engine start
]

,in_flight_tasks:[
#text(size:12pt)[*Complete Assessment Flight — Student as PIC, Instructor as Silent Assessor*]
The instructor does not coach, prompt, or intervene except for safety. All E13 and manoeuvre assessments recorded simultaneously throughout.

_E13 assessment is continuous throughout the complete flight:_

Student conducts the planned sequence:
- Complete pre-flight, startup, taxi, all radio calls from engine start to shutdown
- Takeoff and departure (E8): assessed; circuit departure per AC91-10 — correct procedure and call
- Transponder: correct code set before taxi; squawk ALT once airborne; any code changes managed
- Transit to training area: correct area departure call; tracks on visual landmarks; training area boundaries monitored verbally
- Active listening maintained throughout: student verbalises traffic picture from radio calls and visual scan
- HASSELL check: student completes before the manoeuvre sequence begins and every 15 minutes
- Advanced turning (E9): steep turns, either 45° or 60° AoB
- Scenario stalling (E10): conduct at least one turning stall; HASSELL before sequence; assessed silently
- Forced landing simulation (E14): instructor calls "engine failure"; student manages complete FLWOP sequence; go-around at pre-briefed height — *this constitutes the second S standard flight for E14 if requirements are met*
- Unusual attitude recovery (E16): instructor creates attitude while student is heads-down; student detects and recovers
- Inbound call at 5–10 NM: correct position, altitude, and intentions; assessed for E13
- Overhead join: correct procedure; duty runway identified before descending; non-active side positioning; sequenced correctly; lookout performed
- Downwind: BUMPFISH; downwind radio call; all assessed
- Circuit and landing (E11, E12): assessed
- Simulated radio failure (at instructor's discretion during training): student confirms failure; transmits blind; squawks 7600; describes subsequent actions

#text(size:12pt)[*Instructor Assessment*]
- Records P, S, C, or NC for each manoeuvre element with brief notes
- Records S, C, or NC for each E13 competency variable throughout the flight
- Does not coach, prompt, or intervene except for safety
- If student cannot make a decision and safety is at risk — intervenes, resolves, records the event
]

,common_errors:[
- *Element-specific errors*: Refer to common errors in each preceding Phase 4 lesson plan for remediation guidance.
- *HASSELL not completed*: NC for all manoeuvre elements — non-negotiable.
- *Field selection delay in FLWOP*: Field must be selected before entering the circuit.
- *Radio omissions during transitions*: Most commonly missed during training area exit and inbound calls; these are E13 assessed items.
- *Overhead join procedure incorrect*: Descending before identifying runway in use; wrong side; cutting in front of traffic; all NC for E13 and E15.
- *Active listening not demonstrated*: Transmitting but not updating the traffic picture — assessed for E13.
- *MAYDAY format incomplete during FLWOP simulation*: Callsign, position, problem, plan, POB — all items required.
]

,post_flight:[
- *Student Leads Debrief* (15 min): Student reviews the complete flight; self-assesses each manoeuvre element and each E13 competency variable.
- *Instructor Provides Formal Assessment Results* (15 min):
  - *Manoeuvre elements*: P, S, C, or NC for each with specific comments and evidence
  - *E13 formal assessment*: S, C, or NC for each competency variable with specific evidence
  - NC items (manoeuvre or E13): explain exactly what was observed and what the standard requires; agree remediation plan; do not authorise area solo until NC items are addressed
  - E14 second S standard: confirm whether achieved; if yes, record in training record
  - Area solo gate decision: confirmed or deferred (see standards section)
  - Theory exams: confirm completion status
]

,standards_for_progression:[

#text(size:12pt)[*Area Solo Authorisation Requirements — all must be confirmed*]

_Competency requirements:_
- ☐ E7 (Slow Flight and Stall Recognition) at S standard — Phase 1
- ☐ E10 (Scenario Based Stalling) at S standard — L4.3
- ☐ E14 (Forced Landing and Precautionary Search) at S standard on *two separate flights* — this flight may count as the second
- ☐ E15 (Training Area Operations — departure and joining) at S standard — L4.1
- ☐ E9, E16 at S standard — all manoeuvre elements managed safely
- ☐ *E13 formal assessment passed* — all competency variables at S or above (assessed this lesson)
- ☐ Pre-Solo Air Legislation Exam passed (required before circuit solo)

_E13 competency variables — all must be at S or above:_
- ☐ ERSA home aerodrome entry correctly interpreted (elevation, CTAF, circuit direction, runway details); frequency briefed before departure
- ☐ All mandatory and recommended CTAF calls with correct structure and timing without prompting
- ☐ Active listening maintained; traffic picture verbalised throughout, especially during the overhead join
- ☐ Transponder operated correctly throughout
- ☐ Airspace awareness demonstrated; training area boundaries monitored
- ☐ Radio failure procedure applied correctly without prompting when called
- ☐ MAYDAY format correct; transmitted on Centre; without prompting when called (during FLWOP simulation)
- ☐ Area departure and arrival calls correct; overhead join radio calls correct

_Weather on the day of area solo:_
- ☐ Crosswind at home aerodrome \<5 knots (or within crosswind solo authorisation if C2B complete)
- ☐ Ceiling >2500 ft AGL
- ☐ Visibility >8 km
- ☐ No significant turbulence, windshear, showers, or convective activity in or near the training area
- ☐ Training area weather suitable for planned flight duration

_Additional area solo conditions:_
- ☐ Valid RAAus Student Pilot Certificate held
- ☐ Circuit solo experience established (minimum 2 hours PIC circuit time per C5 requirements)
- ☐ Maintenance release reviewed and briefed by student before every solo flight

_Area solo brief requirements (stated before every area solo):_
- ☐ EFATO plan for today's runway
- ☐ Training area entry and exit procedures
- ☐ Radio failure procedure
- ☐ Forced landing fields in training area identified from chart

#text(size:12pt)[*Weather decision on area solo day:*]

All competency requirements met + All weather conditions met = ✅ Area solo authorised
Any competency requirement not met = ❌ Address requirement first 
All competency requirements met + Weather marginal = ❌ Defer; rebook when conditions improve

- *Outcome*: All elements and E13 competency variables recorded in training record. Area solo authorisation recorded. NC items require remediation before area solo commences.
]

,safety:[
- *Weather*: All Phase 4 exercise minima apply: ceiling >3500 ft AGL for stalling, >2500 ft for other exercises; smooth air preferred; wind \<25 knots
- *Altitude*: HASSELL minimum heights enforced; FLWOP go-around height confirmed before departure; overhead join at 1500 ft AGL
- *Emergency Procedures*: EFATO brief before departure; FLWOP go-around height confirmed
- *TEM*:
  - Assessment flight — instructor maintains non-interventionist stance while remaining safety-ready
  - Overhead join: instructor monitors for traffic conflicts; be prepared to intervene if student is about to descend into conflict
  - Radio failure simulation: student does not actually turn off the radio — simulation only; brief the distinction before departure
  - MAYDAY simulation: transmit on pre-agreed training frequency; do not use CTAF without coordinating with CFI
  - If student shows significant stress affecting safety — end assessment mode; return to coaching; rebook assessment
]

,homework:[
No new homework for this lesson. If area solo was not authorised today due to unmet requirements, identify the specific shortfall and address it before the next flight. If authorised — read the area solo consolidation self-brief template in L4.7 before the first area solo session.
]
)

#show: body => lesson_plan(metadata, lesson, body)